Having a whale of a time! Huge creature spends the afternoon entertaining onlookers by playfully leaping out of the water Whale watching season is flourishing in Sydney's pristine harbour as it's waters continue to be filled with the majestic creatures. One lucky group of spotters had a front-row seat on Sunday afternoon as a playful humpback performed routine tail-slaps and full body breaches out of the water.
